DURBAN - A 36-year-old police officer, Constable Sizwe Norman Sindano, was found unharmed today in Empangeni after he was hijacked and kidnapped on Saturday night.Prem Balram from Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) said Sindano had been hijacked in Waterloo on Saturday night. “A 36-year-old constable based at the Phoenix SAPS was taken with his blue VW Polo after he was hijacked in Bat Road in Waterloo, KZN.”Balram said Sindano had been returning home from a friend's house when he was hijacked by three suspects. In an alert sent out, Balram said the hijacked vehicle had been spotted heading towards Stanger.MORE ON THISArmed robbers open fire at motorist at a PMB petrol station and hijack his bakkieProvincial police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele confirmed that Sindano had been found unharmed today. Constable Sizwe Norman Sindano was found unharmed today in Empangeni after he was hijacked and kidnapped on Saturday. Picture: Reaction Unit South Africa“The member was found safe and not harmed. The vehicle was recovered at Empangeni and it is at Esikhawini pound.”Mbele added that Sindano was unarmed when the incident took place. “The member was not in possession of a firearm during the kidnapping.”THE MERCURY